Ludendo Groupe, which runs toy stores
across  France  and other European nations, may bid for Hamleys
Plc, the U.K. retailer whose flagship London toy store is a
tourist attraction, the  Sunday Times reported , without saying
how it obtained the information.  A deal could be concluded by the end of the month,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
